			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sat Apr 30, 2011 4:30 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>J.M.</strong></div>
				<div class="content">You can start manually transmission by running<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>service transmission.init start</code></dd></dl>If it works (it should, I have it running) you can try<dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>&nbsp;chkconfig transmission.init on</code></dd></dl>to tell transmission to start on each reboot. transmission.init script is in /etc/init.d just in case you want to modify it.</div>
			</div>
			<hr />
		
