			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: Transmission built in.</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sun Jun 12, 2011 3:56 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>J.M.</strong></div>
				<div class="content">I think that keeping the configuration at /etc is not a good idea since it is on the GFH internal memory and it will be written frequently. I put the configuration files in a subfolder of the download directory (/var/axentra/torrentDir/.transmission/). I changed line 22 of /etc/rc.d/init.d/transimission.init file to launch the version 2.31 of transmission with the -g option to set the config directory to the current config dir:<br />        runuser -s /bin/bash 0transmission -c &quot;/opt/bin/transmission-daemon -g /var/axentra/torrentDir/.transmission/ --no-portmap&quot;<br /><br />Everything is going quite well except that the GFH is not responding for a few minutes when I add a file to download. Probably following the wiki <a href="http://www.openstora.com/wiki/index.php?title=Make_your_Stora_responsive_even_while_its_downloading" class="postlink">http://www.openstora.com/wiki/index.php?title=Make_your_Stora_responsive_even_while_its_downloading</a> will solve the problem.</div>
			</div>
